of Illinois to develop outreach kits. These kits were designed to help educate the public about synthetic biology. We worked together to design and create the kits, and then each team distributed them in their own local area.
["Calgary","collaborated","University of Chicago"],["Calgary","collaborated","University of Illinois"]]

SURVEY: VALENCIA
We participated in a survey run by the Valencia team. The survey was designed to gather information about the public's perception of synthetic biology. We helped distribute the survey in our local area and collected responses to send back to the Valencia team.
["Calgary","participated in survey","Valencia"]

WIKI HELP: TOKYO
We helped the Tokyo team with their wiki. They had some technical difficulties and we were able to assist them in resolving these issues.
["Calgary","helped","Tokyo"]

JAMBOREE PRESENTATION: ALBERTA
We worked with the Alberta team to prepare for the Jamboree presentation. We shared resources and ideas to help each other create the best possible presentation.
["Calgary","worked with","Alberta"]

LAB HELP: WATERLOO
We helped the Waterloo team with some lab work. They were having some difficulties with a particular experiment and we were able to provide them with some advice and assistance.
["Calgary","helped","Waterloo"]

MEETUP: WESTERN
We co-organized a meetup with the Western team. This was a great opportunity for us to meet other iGEM teams and share ideas.
["Calgary","co-organized meetup","Western"]

SPONSORSHIP: ADDGENE
We received financial and material support from Addgene. This support was crucial in helping us complete our project.
["Calgary","support from","Addgene"]

of Copenhagen
In the beginning of August, we had a Skype call with iGEM University of Copenhagen. They are working on a project about the degradation of plastic in the ocean. We discussed our projects and shared ideas about how to approach the problem of plastic in the ocean. We also talked about our outreach activities and how we can collaborate in the future. We agreed to keep in touch and update each other about our progress.
